{{Infobox company |name = Brace |logo = BRACE.jpg |type = Private Company |foundation = 2005 |founder = Kya Pate |industry = [[Mixed martial arts]] promotion |homepage = NONE |location_city = Sydney |location_country =[[Australia]] |key_people = Kya Pate, Frank Barca, Jez Margosis }}
'''Brace''' (formerly known as ''Brace For War'') was an [[Australian]] mixed martial arts (MMA) promotion. Brace was founded in 2005 by Kya Pate. In an interview with MMA Kanvas Kya Pate detailed what it is like to be the promoter of Australian MMA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmakanvas.ninemsn.com.au/articles/news/2099/an-insiders-look-whats-it-really-like-to-be-a-fight-promoter.html|title=An insider's look: what's it really like to be a fight promoter?|author=Adam Ireland|date=9 September 2014|website=Mmakanvas.ninemsn.com.au|accessdate=28 August 2017}}</ref>
Since 2009 Brace has staged 50 events in 9 cities over 4 [[Australian States]]. After following the standard MMA format, in 2014 Brace changed to an elimination tournament format based on the style of [[Australian Football League|AFL]], [[NRL]], [[A-League]] soccer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fightnewsaustralia.com/index.php/14-news/488-brace-announce-unique-multi-division-title-tournaments-for-2014?highlight=WyJicmFjZSJd|title=Brace announce unique multi division title tournaments commencing 2014|author=Mike|work=Australian MMA News, Reviews, Interviews & Results|accessdate=28 August 2017}}</ref> 8 Fighters per division compete in knock out elimination rounds all aiming to reach an end of season Grand Final event.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://combatpress.com/2014/11/out-of-obscurity-center-real-fights-14-pfc-7-and-brace-31/|title=Out of Obscurity: Center Real Fights 14, PFC 7 and BRACE 31|author=Bryan Henderson|work=Combat Press|accessdate=28 August 2017}}</ref>
Brace follows the [[Unified Rules of Mixed Martial Arts]].
==Broadcast partners== Brace is broadcast live on [[Network TEN]] exclusively in Australia and [[Fight Network]] based out of Canada
In November 2014, Brace signed a multi year multi event broadcast deal with Network TEN (a major Australian TV network), this is the first for any MMA event within Australia<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmakanvas.ninemsn.com.au/articles/news/2417/aussie-mma-promotion-brace-inks-deal-with-ch10.html|title=Aussie MMA promotion Brace inks deal with Network10|author=Adam Ireland|date=13 November 2014|website=Mmakanvas.ninemsn.com.au|accessdate=28 August 2017}}</ref>
[[UFC Fight Pass]] will begin streaming Brace MMA live events and the promotion’s fight library later in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bracemma.com/brace-signs-with-ufc/# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-12-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222110839/http://www.bracemma.com/brace-signs-with-ufc/# |archive-date=2015-12-22 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ufc.tv/category/brace-mma|title=BRACE MMA|website=Ufc.tv|accessdate=28 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news.com.au/technology/home-entertainment/tv/ufc-and-brace-broker-content-deal-to-broadcast-bouts-across-the-globe-on-ufc-fight-pass/news-story/bdff7e6d9db373b206449c2facf9ec0b|title=UFC’s "Netflix" helping Aussie fighters gain exposure|website=News.com.au|accessdate=28 August 2017}}</ref>
