==Sequel==
{{main|Iron Man 3}}
{{further|List of Marvel Cinematic Universe films}}
After the release of ''Iron Man 2'', [[Walt Disney Studios (division)|Walt Disney Studios]] agreed to pay Paramount at least $115 million for the worldwide distribution rights to ''Iron Man 3'' and ''The Avengers''.<ref name="DisneyIM3" /> Disney, Marvel and Paramount announced a May 3, 2013 release date for ''Iron Man 3''.<ref name="IM3ReleaseDate" /> Shane Black directed ''Iron Man 3'',<ref name="ShaneBlackIM3" /> from a screenplay by [[Drew Pearce]].<ref name="DrewPearceIM3" /> Downey, Paltrow, Cheadle, and Favreau reprised their roles, while [[Ben Kingsley]]<ref name="KingsleyIM3" /> played [[Trevor Slattery]],<ref name="MandarinIM3" /> [[Guy Pearce]] played [[Aldrich Killian]],<ref name="GuyPearceIM3" /> and [[Rebecca Hall]]<ref name="HallIM3" /> played [[Maya Hansen]].<ref name="HansenIM3" />

